<subsection xml:id="subsec-rounding-off-decimal-numbers-to-the-required-decimal-places">
    <title>Rounding off decimal numbers </title>
    <p>
        To round a decimal number to a specified number of decimal places, 
        we examine the digit immediately after the desired decimal place. 
        If this digit is less than <m>5</m>, simply remove all subsequent digits. 
        If the digit is <m>5</m> or greater, we add <m>1</m> to the digit in the desired decimal 
        and eliminate the following digits. 
    </p>
